           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to The Best &a=
mp; The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m <b>John Heilemann</b>, arriving in your inbo=
x on this pitifully gloomy Wednesday in December with a heartening and illu=
minating conversation featuring the venerable leader of the House Democrati=
c caucus, <b>Hakeem Jeffries</b>. We touch on a handful of the Dems=E2=80=
=99 most pressing concerns, not <i>least </i>of which is how, exactly, to r=
econstitute the party in the aftermath of November=E2=80=99s punishing defe=
at. You can find our conversation below the fold. <br/><br/><i>But first, a=
 quick news break from my partner Peter Hamby=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/></p><ul=
 style=3D"margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;margin-top=
:0;margin-bottom:0;list-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li><i=
>A D.N.C. pivot</i>: Members of the Democratic National Committee are meeti=
ng on Wednesday to vote on the process to elect their
next chairman, and, alas, all the candidates so far are men. But I=E2=80=99=
m told that several dozen D.N.C. members are circulating a letter to change=
 how the election itself is conducted=E2=80=94proposing that the committee =
enact ranked-choice voting for the vote in February.<br/><br/>According to =
the letter signed by more than 30 D.N.C. members sent Wednesday to the rule=
s committee, the gist is that ranked-choice voting would make for a less di=
visive election, with fewer hurt feelings, ensuring that party members don=
=E2=80=99t squabble as much over ideology or personal attacks as <b>Donald<=
/b> <b>Trump</b> returns to office next year. Ranked-choice voting, the let=
ter states, =E2=80=9Censures a consensus candidate, reduces negative campai=
gning, and allows voters to fully express their preferences in a large fiel=
d. =E2=80=A6 This approach from our incoming leadership, whomever it may be=
, will ultimately prevent splintering and division among us in the future.=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<i>Peter Hamby</i></li></ul>
          </td>
